function Start(flTimeRemaining)
	
	--Turn on Portal Icon
	Hydra.SetGameVariableFlag("CAP_Tier4_Scos_ArchivesofIssalia_PortalVisiblity")
	
	--Shrines Cleanup
	HOLDOUT_SHRINES = 0
	Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[1])
	Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[2])
	Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[3])
	Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[4])
	
	
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyComplete(S_HOLDOUT_LEVEL_AREA)
	local tSpawners = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("CAP_Tier4_Scos_ArchivesofIssalia_HoldoutSpawners")
	for i, idSpawner in ipairs(tSpawners) do
		if Hydra.ActorIsValid(idSpawner) then
			Hydra.ActorDelete(idSpawner)
		end
	end
	
	local idActorPlayer = Hydra.GetPrimaryPlayer()
	local tplayers = Hydra.PlayerActorsInParty(idActorPlayer)

	--Remove Debuff
	persistantDamageBuff = 0
	if #tplayers > 0 then
		
		for i, idplayer in ipairs(tplayers) do
			Hydra.BuffRemove(HealthDrainDebuff,"HealthDrain",idplayer)
		end
	end	
end

function Start()

--While this may look crazy, there is a method to the madness. The shrines in the room cycle between
--one of four spots. If the player succeeds or fails, we need to immediately turn them off. The 
--HOLDOUT_SHRINES variable can be found in the other callbacks in this phase as well as the previous
--callback in terms of when it equals 1 or 0.

	while (HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) do
	
		if (HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) then
			Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[1])
			Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[4])
			local nCount = 0
				while (nCount < 10 and HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) do
				 Hydra.Wait(1);
				 nCount = nCount + 1;
				end
			nCount = 0
		end
		
		if (HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) then
			Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[2])
			Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[1])
			local nCount = 0
				while (nCount < 10 and HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) do
				 Hydra.Wait(1);
				 nCount = nCount + 1;
				end
			nCount = 0
		end
		
		if (HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) then	
			Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[3])
			Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[2])
			local nCount = 0
				while (nCount < 10 and HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) do
				 Hydra.Wait(1);
				 nCount = nCount + 1;
				end
			nCount = 0
		end
		
		if (HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) then
			Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[4])
			Hydra.BuffRemove(Shrine_VisualBuff,"Buff_Visual",Shrine_Trigger[3])
			local nCount = 0
				while (nCount < 10 and HOLDOUT_SHRINES == 1) do
				 Hydra.Wait(1);
				 nCount = nCount + 1;
				end
			nCount = 0
		end
	end
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, idActorGizmo)
	
	--Enable Holdout Shrines
	HOLDOUT_SHRINES = 1
	
	--Start Boss fight
	Hydra.BossEncounterManuallyQueueStart(S_HOLDOUT_LEVEL_AREA)
	local tSpawners = Hydra.ActorsInGroup("CAP_Tier4_Scos_ArchivesofIssalia_HoldoutSpawners")
	for i, idSpawner in ipairs(tSpawners) do
		Hydra.ActorGizmoSetDisabled(idSpawner,false)
	end
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, sWorldName)
--Turn on Debuff
local idActorPlayer = Hydra.GetPrimaryPlayer()
local tplayers = Hydra.PlayerActorsInParty(idActorPlayer)

	if  (persistantDamageBuff == 1) then
		if #tplayers > 0 then
			
			for i, idplayer in ipairs(tplayers) do
				Hydra.BuffApplyToTarget(HealthDrainDebuff,"HealthDrain",idplayer)
			end
		end	
	end
end
